From: art-suite conda packaging
Subject: [PATCH] Drop -Werror so art builds under conda's newer libstdc++

art is the largest compiled product in the suite and builds with the same
VIGILANT + WERROR + -pedantic flag combination that already turned a benign
[[nodiscard]] warning into a hard error in canvas (#6). Over art's far larger
surface, conda-forge's newer libstdc++/gcc emits additional vigilant warnings
that WERROR would promote to errors. cetmodules' WERROR keyword has no external
off-switch (CXXFLAGS can't win the flag ordering -- see
conda/potential_improvements.md #2), so we remove the WERROR keyword from
cet_set_compiler_flags. This reproduces upstream's runtime behavior exactly
(no source/logic change) while letting the build complete.

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -23,7 +23,6 @@
 cet_cmake_module_directories(Modules BINARY)
 
 cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS VIGILANT DWARF_VER 4
-  WERROR
   NO_UNDEFINED
   EXTRA_FLAGS -pedantic)
 
